<tr><td><table role="presentation" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="background-color:#0F2237;">
<tr><td class="mp" style="padding:52px 56px 40px;text-align:center;">
  <p style="margin:0 0 14px;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.3em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(245,240,229,0.4);">A NOTE FROM ANDREW</p>
  <h1 class="ht" style="margin:0 0 8px;font-family:'Cormorant',Georgia,serif;font-weight:300;font-size:42px;line-height:1.08;color:#F5F0E5;">Earn the <em style='font-style:italic;font-weight:400;color:#E8834A;'>Line.</em></h1>
  <p style="margin:0;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:400;color:rgba(245,240,229,0.45);">The one rule that eliminates your most common error</p>
</td></tr></table></td></tr>
<tr><td class="mp" style="padding:36px 56px 0;"><p style="margin:0 0 20px;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15.5px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.85;color:rgba(27,58,92,0.68);">Hey %FIRSTNAME%,</p><p style="margin:0 0 20px;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15.5px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.85;color:rgba(27,58,92,0.68);">I want to show you the most common mistake I see on the courts &mdash; from beginners to 4.0 players. It&rsquo;s not a technical problem. It&rsquo;s a decision problem. And once you see it, you can&rsquo;t unsee it.</p><p style="margin:0 0 20px;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15.5px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.85;color:rgba(27,58,92,0.68);">Here it is: <strong style='color:#1B3A5C;'>going down the line on a deep ball.</strong></p><p style="margin:0 0 20px;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15.5px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.85;color:rgba(27,58,92,0.68);">The opponent hits a solid shot to your forehand. It lands past the service line. You&rsquo;re still moving, your weight is shifting, your feet aren&rsquo;t set &mdash; and you try to rip it down the line. It clips the tape or sails wide by three inches.</p><p style="margin:0 0 20px;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15.5px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.85;color:rgba(27,58,92,0.68);">You blame the forehand. But the forehand was fine.</p><p style="margin:0 0 20px;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15.5px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.85;color:rgba(27,58,92,0.68);">The shot <em>selection</em> was wrong.</p><p style="margin:0 0 20px;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15.5px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.85;color:rgba(27,58,92,0.68);">Down the line is the hardest shot in tennis. The net is six inches higher at the sideline than in the center. The court is shorter. The margin for error is roughly half of what you get crosscourt. And you chose that shot at the worst possible moment &mdash; off-balance, on a deep ball, with your feet still moving.</p></td></tr><tr><td class="mp" style="padding:24px 56px 0;">
<table role="presentation" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="background-color:#0F2237;border-radius:10px;">
<tr><td style="padding:28px 32px;">
  <p style="margin:0 0 12px;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#E8834A;">THE LBTA FRAMEWORK &mdash; EARN THE LINE</p>
  <p style="margin:0 0 12px;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.75;color:rgba(245,240,229,0.65);">The rule is simple: <strong style='color:#F5F0E5;'>don&rsquo;t go down the line unless the ball is short enough for your feet to be set and balanced.</strong></p><p style="margin:0 0 12px;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.75;color:rgba(245,240,229,0.65);">Deep ball &rarr; crosscourt. Every time. No exceptions.</p><p style="margin:0 0 12px;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.75;color:rgba(245,240,229,0.65);">Short ball, feet set, weight forward &rarr; <em>now</em> you&rsquo;ve earned the right to change direction.</p><p style="margin:0 0 12px;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.75;color:rgba(245,240,229,0.65);">We teach this to our 9-year-olds in Green Dot. We teach it to our HP players. We teach it in every adult group. This one rule, applied consistently, eliminates more unforced errors than any grip change, any swing fix, any new racquet.</p>
  <p style="margin:0;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.75;color:rgba(245,240,229,0.65);"><strong style="color:#2E8B8B;">Try it this week:</strong> Play a set where you&rsquo;re only allowed to go down the line on a short ball. If the ball lands deep, crosscourt is your only option. Count how many errors just disappear.</p>
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td class="mp" style="padding:16px 56px 0;"><p style="margin:0;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.7;color:rgba(27,58,92,0.45);">Spring programs are running at all three locations through June 13. <a href="https://www.lagunabeachtennisacademy.com/schedules" style="color:#2E8B8B;font-weight:600;">Full schedule &rarr;</a></p></td></tr><tr><td class="mp" style="padding:24px 56px 0;">
  <table role="presentation" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,rgba(46,139,139,0.15) 20%,rgba(232,131,74,0.1) 80%,transparent);"></td></tr></table>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class="mp" style="padding:16px 56px 0;">
  <p style="margin:0 0 20px;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15.5px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.85;color:rgba(27,58,92,0.68);">This is one of 19 decision rules we use across every program. The insight isn&rsquo;t complicated. The discipline to apply it under pressure &mdash; that&rsquo;s what practice is for.</p><p style="margin:0 0 20px;font-family:'DM Sans',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15.5px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.85;color:rgba(27,58,92,0.68);">See you on the courts.</p>
